quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  23,1,"Surely the believers have attained success:"
  23,2,"those who are reverent in their prayers;"
  23,3,"and those who disregard idle talk;"
  23,4,"and those who are observant of the purifying charity{1};",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is <i>zakāt</i>, which denotes purification and growth.
  23,5,"and those who preserve their private parts,"
  23,6,"except from their spouses or those whom they rightfully possess—for then they are free from blame."
  23,7,"But whoever seeks anything beyond that—those are the transgressors."
  23,8,"And those who to their trusts{1}and their covenant are faithful,",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Ibn Kathir read it as: “…their trust…”
  23,9,"and those who preserve their prayers{1}—",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…their prayer…”
  23,10,"those are the ones who are the<i>(true) </i>inheritors"
